longBusinessSummary: Finnair Oyj operates in the airline business in North Atlantic, Asia, Europe, Middle East, and internationally. The company offers Finnair and oneworld global network, passenger and cargo traffic, ancillary services, package tours under the Aurinkomatkat-Suntours brand name, and other travel products; and support services comprising catering, aircraft maintenance, ground handling, and airline training. As of December 31, 2023, it operated through a fleet of 55 aircrafts, which included 25 wide-body and 30 narrowbody aircrafts. Finnair Oyj was incorporated in 1923 and is headquartered in Vantaa, Finland.
